---
Description: Documentation Conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

## READMEs
- Use sentence case for headings
- Include a "Quick Start" section that gets someone running in 5 minutes
- Code examples should be complete and runnable

## Code comments
- Document "why" not "what" in inline comments
- Don't comment obvious code

## HTTP / protocol documentation
- Document scan-related HTTP behavior in **MkDocs** (see `docs/`, `mkdocs.yaml`): getting started, configuration, troubleshooting, and protocol notes.
- Prefer **example requests/responses** in prose or fenced blocks where they help operators (SOAP/XML for `/wsd`, uploads for `/scan`).
- Document **error and failure** paths (HTTP status, common faults), not only success cases.

